**◌ the mythos —** Dussutour's finding (2016): the mold learns to ignore a harmless irritant it must cross — and a habituated mold can transfer that learned state to a naive one by fusing. The simplest learning, in a single cell. a cell, concept, or pioneer of the brainless mind

